riscv-mini-os
=============

Origin
------
A small amount of build scaffolding (Makefile structure, header
conventions, device-driver stubs, test-bench harness) was authored by
prior contributors and is distributed under the NCSA Open Source
License (see LICENSE). All starter source files retain their original
copyright notices and SPDX-License-Identifier headers; removing or
modifying those notices is not permitted under the NCSA license terms.

Modifications and additions
---------------------------
The substantive kernel implementation -- the memory subsystem, virtual
memory, process model, syscall layer, KTFS read/write driver,
scheduler, traps, page-fault handling, ELF loader integration, fork/
exec semantics, the test-bench cases, the user-mode shell, the pure-
Python `mkfs_ktfs` toolchain, the documentation, and the CI
configuration -- were authored by Yoonkyu Lee in 2024-2026 and are
also distributed under the NCSA Open Source License.

